section.painting-portfolioPage
  .container
    .row
      .col.l12.m12.s12#workSlideshow
        .carousel.carousel-slider.center(data-indicators='true')
          .carousel-item.white-text(href='#one!')
            img(src='/assets/imgs/portfolioWork/visualArt/painting/letMeHelpYou/lmhy1.jpg')
          .carousel-item.white-text(href='#two!')
            img(src='/assets/imgs/portfolioWork/visualArt/painting/letMeHelpYou/lmhy2.jpg')

    .row
      .col.l1
        button.togglePortfolioCopy.waves-effect.waves-light
          i.fa.fa-chevron-up(aria-hidden='true')
      .col.l5.m2
        p#workSubHeading TOGGLE WORK DESCRIPTION
      .col.l1.m2.s4.offset-l5.offset-m3
        ul.center-align
          li#portfolioPageNext
            a(href='painting-transfig.html')
              i.fa.fa-chevron-right(aria-hidden='true').right.waves-effect
    .row.portfolioCopy
      .col.l4.m4.s12
        h3.workTitle Let Me Help You
        h6.push-leading.workSubHeading 2015
        p.workSubHeading PAINTING
          p.workDescription
            | Let Me Help You is a work which asks the viewer to contemplate the various
            | modes of production in art, the body's relationship to the viewed work, and
            | if one may be imaginative, the implications of self-referential art.
      .col.l4.m4.s12
        p.workDescription.pushDown
          | As part of an internal investigation with history, and how history can be
          | embedded or removed from a work, Let Me Help You repurposes the building
          | materials from sculptures and paintings of the past. Adorned on an acrylic
          | pedestal high above the viewer sits a 3-d printed abstract form with a mirror
          | pointed at it.
      .col.l1.m1.s1
        ul.center-align
          li#next
            a(href='painting-transfig.html')
              i.fa.fa-chevron-right(aria-hidden='true').right.waves-effect
